ure coding guidelines shouldminimize the number of security vulnerabilitiesintroduced through poor coding practices. Trainingfor developers may be provided in-house or by thirdparties and should be applicable for technologyused.As industry-accepted secure coding practiceschange organizational coding practices anddeveloper training should likewise be updated toaddress new threats\\u2014for example memoryscraping attacks.The vulnerabilities identified in 6.5.1 through 6.5.10provide a minimum baseline. It is up to theorganization to remain up to date with vulnerabilitytrends and incorporate appropriate measures intotheir secure coding practices.\",\"compliance_package_id\":4,\"workflow_owner_id\":null,\"workflow_status\":0,\"created\":\"2023-01-18T13:19:21+00:00\",\"modified\":\"2023-01-18T13:19:21+00:00\",\"deleted\":0,\"deleted_date\":null}',0,0,NULL,'Admin Admin','1',NULL,6,'192.168.23.1','/compliance-package-items/add?modalId=1&_=1674047869066&ImportTool=1','2023-01-18 13:19:21'),('c469a65e-e7de-4908-bd1c-f49b7211aef4',1,'CREATE',NULL,'ComplianceManagements','6','0220e43d-fffe-4f45-9de7-e01dfea4457c','{\"id\":6,\"compliance_package_item_id\":6,\"compliance_treatment_strategy_id\":null,\"legal_id\":null,\"owner_id\":null,\"efficacy\":0,\"description\":\"\",\"workflow_owner_id\":null,\"workflow_status\":0,\"created\":\"2023-01-18T13:19:21+00:00\",\"modified\":\"2023-01-18T13:19:21+00:00\",\"edited\":null,\"deleted\":0,\"deleted_date\":null,\"assets\":null,\"business_continuities\":null,\"third_party_risks\":null,\"risks\":null,\"compliance_analysis_findings\":null,\"compliance_exceptions\":null,\"security_services\":null,\"projects\":null,\"owners\":null}',0,0,NULL,'Admin Admin','1',NULL,15,'192.168.23.1','/compliance-package-items/add?modalId=1&_=1674047869066&ImportTool=1','2023-01-18 13:19:21'),('c4c47e36-9f2e-40a7-849a-aac40f8aa39d',1,'CREATE',NULL,'CompliancePackageItems','47','a0751f76-f22a-4748-b58d-9cb1f260ecba','{\"id\":47,\"item_id\":\"5.2.0\",\"name\":\"En